SIMPLE: waltz
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waltz
<hw>Waltz</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. <ets>walzer</ets>,
from <ets>walzen</ets> to roll, revolve, dance, OHG. <ets>walzan</ets>
to roll; akin to AS. <ets>wealtan</ets>. See <er>Welter</er>.]</ety>
<def>A dance performed by two persons in circular figures with a
whirling motion; also, a piece of music composed in triple measure for
this kind of dance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waltz</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Waltz
<hw>Waltz</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Waltzed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Waltzing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To dance a waltz.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waltzer</ent>⟦br⟧
